    "insertion": {
      "title": "Orbit insertion (at apsis)",
      "description": "Coasts to the next periapsis (or apoapsis), then burns there: circular (v = √(μ/r)) or elliptical with a chosen opposite apsis (vis-viva). At-apoapsis + circular is the classic launch-circularization (OMS-2) burn. Preserves the orbit plane.",
